cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV

The paper discusses the application of reinforcement learning to complex autonomous robots, which involves perception through many sensors and parallel actions using many actuators. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Robotics (cs.RO), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. The paper also proposes an algorithm that takes advantage of the categorizability of the environment, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper reports results of the application of the algorithm to simulated robotic problems, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
